ourses about freedom within these three traditions. The book offers fundamental knowledge about the specific understanding of freedom in each one of these traditions, their interdependencies and their relationship to secular interpretations.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLibertyxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aLibertyxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aLibertyxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 0aReligionsxRelations. 4aDialog. 4aFreiheit. 4aInterreligiosität. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh  aInterfaith relations.  aInterreligious dialogue.  afreedom.1 aEl Kaisy-Friemuth, Maha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMännle, Ursula, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSeeskin, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTamer, Georges, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTamer, Georges, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aThörner, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVorster, Nico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2019 Part 1z978311076246408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishz978311061685908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishz978311061074108iTitle is part of eBook package